### **Write a good cover letter**

Talk about unique things in the job description like “JavaScript Sever” or “slider jquery plugin”

Don’t include any script or predefined text like “I have read your requirement …. or I have Experienced, etc. “

Instead of this write the content from the job description.

Try to send the Video message if possible

### **Answer the Set of Questions**

There are 2 types of questions in the job proposal

1\. Static — Don’t leave them blank and answer

2\. Custom — Specifically written by the client. We should be more focused on this.

### **Try to Give Value on the first impression**

If the client is asking about any problem, try to give a suggestion as a reply to them. Example — No sales on the website — Suggestion — Check SSL Certificate

### **Prepare Scope Document**

Create a Scope document that defines things like In Scope — Out Scope — Production support, etc.

### **Conclusion**

It was a fun filled day with the things like “Meet Like minded people” gain knowledge about the “process of Freelancing” and “do and don’t about the same”.

